# Opportunity Review: Solicitation W81K0226U0001 – Military Hospital Laundry Services 

---

## Overview
- **Solicitation Number:** W81K0226U0001
- **Title:** Military Hospital Laundry Services
- **Agency:** Department of Defense, Department of the Army, US Army Medical Command
- **Type:** Sources Sought Notice (market research, not a contract or RFP)

## Key Dates
- **Posted:** November 6, 2025
- **Response Deadline:** November 20, 2025, at 10:00 AM Pacific Time

## Scope & Description
- **Services Required:** Laundry services for Madigan Army Medical Center (MAMC) at Joint Base Lewis McChord (JBLM), Tacoma, Washington
- **NAICS Code:** 812332 – Industrial Launderers
- **PSC:** S209 – Housekeeping: Laundry/Drycleaning
- **Eligible Size Standard:** $47M USD
- **Primary Scope:** Non-personal laundry services in a medical facility (must meet The Joint Commission standards)
- **Location:** Tacoma, WA (JBLM)

## Included Documents / Attachments
**DRAFT PWS and other exhibits/attachments referenced, including:**
- Performance Requirements Summary, Contractor Deliverables
- Government Furnished Property list
- Packaging Standards
- Linen/Item Volume Charts
- Quality Assurance Surveillance Plan, Wage Determination, Price Matrix, Historical Workload Data, etc. (**some "under separate file"**)

## Insurance Requirements
- **Not detailed** in the sources sought but expected in future solicitation documents.

