## Qualifications & Flags
- **QUALIFIERS:**
  - Fits Powerlink’s facility services model (laundry)
  - US-based
  - Meets operational scope standards
- **DISQUALIFIERS/FLAGS:**
  - Not a direct solicitation (sources sought only)
  - Insurance/bonding specifics pending
  - Response window: 2 weeks (acceptable, but tight)
  - Clinical care is NOT required per context (no disqualifier)
  - Located in Washington State (no location disqualifier)
  - Complex compliance (TJC, DoD security access)
  - Union agreements & capital assets not mentioned, but should be verified in full RFP

## Submission Instructions
- Response by email in .doc, .pdf, or body text
- DO NOT include proprietary or sensitive info
- Questions via email only (no calls)
- Identification of business size required
- Not procurements—no guarantee of contract

## Summary Risks & Opportunities
- **Risks:** Insurance requirements TBD; scope of services and volumes must be confirmed in future documentation. Security/regulatory compliance may be complex for base entry.
- **Opportunities:** Fit for EVS/laundry providers, strong market research entry for follow-on RFP. Large medical laundry volume. Clear, documented scope by Army Medical.

## Action Recommendations 
- Monitor SAM.gov and contact POCs for detailed PWS/attachments.
- Proceed only if insurance and union/capital asset requirements are confirmed as feasible when full RFP is issued.

